      "description": "The **Users** folder contains all endpoints related to user management and authentication in the Booking App backend. These routes allow you to register new users, manage existing accounts, and handle secure login with token-based authentication.\n\n🔑 Key Features\n\n- `POST /users` → Register a new user\n    \n- `POST /users/login` → Authenticate and obtain a token\n    \n- **Private access (requires Bearer token):**\n    \n- `GET /users` → Retrieve all registered users\n    \n- `PUT /users/:id` → Update user details by ID\n    \n- `DELETE /users/:id` → Remove a user by ID\n    \n\n🧩 Model\n\nEach user record includes:\n\n- `id` (primary key)\n    \n- `firstName`\n    \n- `lastName`\n    \n- `email`\n    \n- `password` (securely stored)\n    \n- `gender`\n    \n\n🔒 Security\n\n- Login generates a JWT or token stored in `{{authToken}}`.\n    \n- All private endpoints require the token in the Authorization header.\n    \n- Passwords are never exposed in responses."
    },
