      "description": "The **Cities** folder contains all endpoints related to managing city records in the Booking App backend. These routes allow you to create, update, delete, and list cities, which serve as the foundation for associating hotels with their geographic location.\n\n🔑 Key Features\n\n- `GET /cities` → Retrieve all available cities\n    \n- **Private access (requires Bearer token):**\n    \n- `POST /cities` → Create a new city\n    \n- `PUT /cities/:id` → Update an existing city by ID\n    \n- `DELETE /cities/:id` → Remove a city by ID\n    \n\n🧩 Model\n\nEach city record includes:\n\n- `id` (primary key)\n    \n- `name` (e.g., Guadalajara, Bogotá, New York)\n    \n- `country` (full country name)\n    \n- `countryId` (string code, e.g., MX, CO, US)\n    \n\n📊 Dataset\n\nThe backend is seeded with **30 cities**, ensuring diverse test data for hotel associations and queries.\n\n🔒 Security\n\n- Only authenticated users can create, update, or delete cities.\n    \n- Public endpoints allow anyone to browse the list of cities."
    },
