      "description": "The **Hotels** folder contains all endpoints related to hotel management in the Booking App backend. These routes allow you to browse, filter, create, update, and delete hotel records, as well as retrieve detailed information about each property.\n\n🔑 Key Features\n\n- `GET /hotels` → Retrieve all hotels, with optional queries for `name` and `cityId`.\n    \n    - Example: `/hotels?name=Four Seasons&cityId=1`\n        \n    - Each hotel includes an **average** field showing the mean rating from its reviews.\n        \n- `GET /hotels/:id` → Retrieve a single hotel by ID.\n    \n- **Private access (requires Bearer token):**\n    \n- `POST /hotels` → Create a new hotel record.\n    \n- `PUT /hotels/:id` → Update hotel details by ID.\n    \n- `DELETE /hotels/:id` → Remove a hotel by ID.\n    \n\n🧩 Model\n\nEach hotel record includes:\n\n- `id` (primary key)\n    \n- `name`\n    \n- `description`\n    \n- `price`\n    \n- `address`\n    \n- `lat` (latitude)\n    \n- `lon` (longitude)\n    \n- `cityId` (reference to the city)\n    \n\n📊 Dataset\n\nThe backend is seeded with **150 hotels**, each linked to one of the 30 available cities. Hotels are enriched with images, reviews, and booking data to support realistic testing scenarios.\n\n🔒 Security\n\n- Public endpoints allow anyone to explore hotels and their details.\n    \n- Private endpoints require authentication with a valid token."
    },
