      "description": "The **Bookings** folder contains all endpoints related to hotel reservations in the Booking App backend. These routes allow logged-in users to create, view, update, and delete their reservations, ensuring a secure and personalized booking experience.\n\n🔑 Key Features\n\n- **Private access (requires Bearer token):**\n    \n- `GET /bookings` → Retrieve all bookings of the logged-in user.\n    \n- `POST /bookings` → Create a new booking. The `userId` is automatically inferred from the authenticated user.\n    \n- `PUT /bookings/:id` → Update booking dates (`checkIn` and `checkOut` only). `userId` and `hotelId` cannot be modified.\n    \n- `DELETE /bookings/:id` → Cancel a booking by ID.\n    \n\n🧩 Model\n\nEach booking record includes:\n\n- `id` (primary key)\n    \n- `checkIn` (date)\n    \n- `checkOut` (date)\n    \n- `userId` (linked to logged-in user)\n    \n- `hotelId` (linked to hotel)\n    \n\n📊 Dataset\n\nThe backend is seeded with **300+ bookings**, providing realistic scenarios for testing reservation flows, date updates, and cancellations.\n\n🔒 Security\n\n- All booking endpoints are private and require authentication.\n    \n- The system ensures that users can only access and manage their own reservations."
