      "description": "The **Reviews** folder contains all endpoints related to hotel reviews in the Booking App backend. These routes allow users to share feedback about their stays, manage their own reviews, and browse reviews from other guests with pagination and filtering options.\n\n🔑 Key Features\n\n- `GET /reviews` → Retrieve all reviews.\n    \n    - Supports queries for `hotelId` to filter reviews by hotel.\n        \n    - Supports `offset` and `perPage` for pagination (e.g., `/reviews?hotelId=1&offset=0&perPage=10`).\n        \n- **Private access (requires Bearer token):**\n    \n- `POST /reviews` → Create a new review. The `userId` is automatically inferred from the logged-in user.\n    \n- `PUT /reviews/:id` → Update an existing review (only `rating` and `comment` can be modified).\n    \n- `DELETE /reviews/:id` → Remove a review by ID.\n    \n\n🧩 Model\n\nEach review record includes:\n\n- `id` (primary key)\n    \n- `rating` (numeric score)\n    \n- `comment` (text feedback)\n    \n- `userId` (linked to the logged-in user)\n    \n- `hotelId` (linked to the hotel being reviewed)\n    \n\n📊 Dataset\n\nThe backend is seeded with **100+ reviews**, providing realistic scenarios for testing hotel ratings, user feedback, and pagination queries.\n\n🔒 Security\n\n- Public endpoints allow anyone to browse reviews.\n    \n- Private endpoints require authentication, ensuring users can only create, update, or delete their own reviews."
